[2mproject_goal: Build a personal project tracker web app using Django with a SQLite database and HTML/JS frontend
success_criteria:
  - Django REST endpoints for CRUD operations on projects, tasks, and tags
  - Each project has a name, description, status (active/completed/archived), and created date
  - Each task belongs to a project and has a title, status (todo/in_progress/done), priority (low/medium/high), and due date
  - Tags can be assigned to both projects and tasks (many-to-many)
  - Frontend has separate views for projects list, project detail (showing its tasks), and a tag filter view
  - Adding/editing/deleting entities works without full page reload
  - Dashboard view showing summary stats (total projects, tasks by status, overdue tasks)
  - Data persists in SQLite database
context_notes:
  - Use Django with SQLite backend
  - Frontend is plain HTML, CSS, and vanilla JS (no React/Vue/Angular)
  - Django serves both the API and static/template files
  - All code lives in apps/project-tracker/
  - Use Django models with proper foreign key and many-to-many relationships
constraints:
  - Django and its built-in dependencies only, no additional pip packages (no DRF, no celery, etc.)
  - No frontend JS frameworks
  - Single Django project, no microservices[0m
